               <msContents defective="false">
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1" defective="false">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the donors.&#xD;
Six lines in the incipit page of Text I-1 (fol. 4r), in three groups, alternating with black lines; incipits of the texts, their sections and subsections; six lines in the incipit page of the section “Friday morning” (Text I-8), in three groups, alternating with black lines.&#xD;
Titles of the Biblical books and other works; names of Hebrew letters in Text I-8; abbreviations in Text I-7 and Text I-8; the beginning word of each paragraph in the text “Tǝmḫǝrtä ḫǝbuʾat” within Text I-9; the words yǝbe in Text I-4 (esp. fols. 17vb-18rc) and Text I-6 (esp. fols. 53vc-54ra); the words yǝtärägwǝm in Text I-6 and Text I-8, mätärgwäm in Text I-8, wä-yǝbäl/wä-yǝbälu in Text I-8, ṣällǝyu in Text I-9.&#xD;
Elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements; elements of the text dividers.</rubric>
